commitResults.messageBody:
For Level-7,
*Add initialise function to read tasks from file to chabot once its opened.
*Modify added function to enable appending of new tasks into file.
*Add editWrite function to replace the tasks in the file with those active in the list in the chatbot as it is hard to edit the file to mark/unmark/delete tasks.

For Coding Standards,
*Rewrite imports by replacing wildcard import with specific ones.
*As horizontalLine is a constant replace it with HORIZONTAL_LINE.
Creates ./data dir and tasks.txt file if they are not present.

Updated Duke.java deadline and event function to create LocalDateTime object of by, from and to variables in a "dd-MM-yyyy HH:mm" from input date/time string. Added error handling for when date/time format in input string is incorrect.

Updated Deadline.java and Event.java to take LocalDateTime for variables by, from and to instead of String. Additionally updated their toString method to print out date/time in a different format from what was given by user as required.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add toFile() function to Task, ToDo, Deadline and Event Classes
commitResults.messageBody: Add this function to make it easier to write to the file later on, instead of using additional arguments or instanceof.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add minimal classes required for A-MoreOOP
commitResults.messageBody:
Ui
*opens scanner and uses it to read commands from user in readCommand().
*All other methods are used to print responses to commands to user.

Storage
*load(): reads tasks from given file when chatbot is opened and returns a ArrayList<Task>.
*saveAdd(): adds tasks to file for todo/deadline/event commands.
*saveRewrite: rewrites entire file using TaskList for mark/unmark/delete commands.

TaskList
*encapsulates a ArrayList<Task> which can be initialised using two constuctors one which creates a new list and another that references a existing list.
*get(), size(), add() and delete() methods to use for commands.

Parser
*parseFile(): to read from File and add corresponding Task object to a TaskList.
*parseCommand(): to read commands from user and create corresponding Command Object.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add *Command Classes and a abstract Command Class
commitResults.messageBody:
Classes:
*Command {abstract}
*AddCommand for todo/deadline/event, takes in a Task object
*ListCommand for list
*MarkCommand for mark and unmark takes in a int index for task in list
*DeleteCommand for delete takes in a int index for task in list
*ExitCommand for bye
*InvalidCommand for non-existent commands throws exception

Each Class has 2 methods
*execute(): implements command using TaskList, Ui and Storage
*isExit(): tells whether it is a ExitCommand object

* A-MoreOOP:
  Update Duke.java for A-MoreOOP
  Add *Command Classes and a abstract Command Class
  Add minimal classes required for A-MoreOOP
  Add toFile() function to Task, ToDo, Deadline and Event Classes

Organise into a alastor package where all Command classes are in a sub-package called command and all Task classes are in a sub-package called task.

Rename "Duke" Duke.java and DukeException.java(and all instances of DukeException) to "Alastor" as Rename in level-0 was only done to strings.
Deleted Duke.java and DukeException.java to do so and created corresponding replacements. For unknown reason staged files show deletion of only DukeException of the two.
It also shows Command.java and InvalidCommand.java being deleted and new ones being created even though they were not deleted.

* branch-A-Packages:
  Organise into packages and Rename

  Add Gradle support

commitResults.messageTitle: Override equals() for relevant Task Classes
commitResults.messageBody:
This is done so that assertEquals can use it to check whether two Task objects are equal.
Did not need to do so for ToDo as the one in Task is sufficient but the other two types require overriding.

*Introduce enum ParseType to distinguish parsing file and parsing commands from using and giving corresponding error message.
*Add parameter to stringToDate() to account for ParseType.
*Rename checkForEmpty() to checkParameter() and Add parameter to account for ParseType. Additionally now it checks whether there is a missing or extra parameters.
*Update error messages
*Add checkParameter() in parseFile() to check whether file is corrupted. Also added Default in switch statement and check for marking value(either 0 or 1) in case file is corrupted.
Tests parserFile() function in 2 scenarios, one where the file in intact and the other where it is corrupted.

Tests load() method in 3 scenarios:
* where file exists
* where file does not exist
* where the directory the file is expected to be in (and the file) do not exist.
